supports HTML5 video Miami CitizenM hotel, CitizenM newest in the center of the city has been launched. The hotel has a total of 252 rooms. The rooms are spread over the hotel’s 20 stories. The rooms are all identical in size and design. They will feature king beds, wall-to-wall windows, free WiFi, and streaming TVs. As part of an Open Art Call that citizenM held with 70 different artists earlier this year. The rooms have artwork from 10 different artists. The hotel’s unconventional living room-style lobby welcomes visitors with furniture by Swiss designers Vitra. Additionally, the literature and artwork that is meant to evoke the feeling of being at home. The hotel provides canteenM, one of the brand’s hallmark eateries, which is open 24 hours a day in the lobby and serves food and beverages. Also Read: Construction Breaks Ground on Okan Mixed-Use Tower in Miami Furthermore, the Miami CitizenM hotel has two patios for guests to use. One of the patios faces S. Miami Avenue. The other faces one of the greenest gardens in the city. Along with eight conference rooms and a rooftop pool reserved just for hotel guests, the new Miami hotel will also be citizenM’s first public appearance. This year, citizenM, which describes itself as an “upscale hotel” firm, will open two hotels in Miami. The hotel chain now operates 27 properties in 17 locations, including London, Amsterdam, Paris, Geneva, New York, Boston, San Francisco, Taipei, and Kuala Lumpur. “We’re excited to debut the first of Miami’s two citizenM hotels this year. We are thrilled to be able to offer guests an unmatched and culturally rich experience, making this property a landmark in Miami’s Brickell neighborhood, Robin Chadha, citizenM CMO said. The interior has been curated with a selection of works from artists celebrating Miami’s diverse and vivacious spirit.